FBIS4-10720 "drlat074_m_94005" FBIS-LAT-94-074 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 Brazil Debt Agreement Closed in New York Debt Agreement Closed in New York PY1604004494 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in Portuguese 2300 GMT 15 Apr 94 PY1604004494 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television Portuguese BFN [Text] After three years of negotiations, Brazil has closed its foreign debt agreement. The country will pay $51 billion over 30 years, representing a 30 percent discount. A maneuver by the Brazilian negotiators thwarted threats by the Dart family, which holds Brazilian foreign debt papers and does not agree with the discount. The Dart family was threatening to file an international lawsuit against Brazil for failure to pay.
